Sanjay Leela Bhansali’s epic drama Padmaavat was one of the most controversial film releases in Indian cinema. Even before its release, the film sparked intense public debate over the portrayal of Rani Padmavati. After its premiere, the climax scene continued to fuel discussions across audiences. Yet, despite all the controversy, one thing remains undeniable — Padmaavat was a cinematic marvel that beautifully captured the story and spirit of Queen Padmavati through Bhansali’s signature storytelling.
